Method Detail

getDivergentSiteOmegas

public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Double> getDivergentSiteOmegas()
Getter method for the estimated site omega (dN/dS) ratios, for sites under divergent selection only.
These are calculated from PAML as the product of the category BEB probabilities * the category dN/dS estimates.
Differs from getAllSiteOmegas() in that only sites in third (divergent) site category BEB ³ 0.50 are returned.

Returns:
HashMap <Integer,Double>: a HashMap containing divergent site indices and their calculated product omegas.
See Also:
CladeModelOutput#getAllSiteOmegas()}
